events.name: LSU Tigers at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Ron Brooks returned an interception for a touchdown 28 seconds into the game and top-ranked LSU never looked back, piling up 353 yards rushing on the way to a 52-3 rout of Mississippi on Saturday night.

events.name: Georgia Southern Eagles at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Trent Richardson rushed for 175 yards and scored three touchdowns to power No. 3 Alabama to a 45-21 victory over Georgia Southern on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Richardson's 3 TDs lift Bama past Ga. Southern

events.name: USC Trojans at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Matt Barkley threw for 323 yards and four touchdowns and the USC Trojans (No. 18 AP)  held off No. 4 Oregon on Saturday night when Alejandro Maldonado missed a 37-yard field goal to tie the game with five seconds left.

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Robert Griffin III and Baylor created even more chaos in the national championship race with a stunning blow against fifth-ranked Oklahoma.

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Tyler Wilson had a school-record 32 completions as No. 6 Arkansas defeated Mississippi State 44-17.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arkansas gears up for LSU by crushing Miss. St.

events.name: Clemson Tigers at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description: Mike Glennon threw three touchdown passes and North Carolina State shut down No. 7 Clemson's explosive offense to help the Wolfpack beat the mistake-prone Tigers 37-13 on Saturday.

events.name: California Golden Bears at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: No. 8 Stanford 31, California 28
headlines.shortLinkText: Luck, Stanford survive slow start, hold off Cal

events.name: Boise State Broncos at San Diego State Aztecs

headlines.description: Kellen Moore completed 28 of 40 passes for 366 yards and four touchdowns, three to Tyler Shoemaker, and the No. 10 Broncos benefited from three San Diego State turnovers to race to a 52-35 victory Saturday night.

events.name: SMU Mustangs at Houston Cougars

headlines.description: Case Keenum set the Football Bowl Subdivision career record for completions, threw a touchdown pass and ran for another score as No. 11 Houston stayed unbeaten with a 37-7 win over SMU on Saturday.

events.name: The Citadel Bulldogs at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Connor Shaw threw for 217 yards and three touchdowns, including Alshon Jeffery's first scoring catch in more than a month, and South Carolina defeated The Citadel 34-20 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 12 South Carolina takes care of The Citadel

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: A week after a wild overtime thriller, Collin Klein and the Wildcats survived a dominating performance by the Texas defense for a rugged 17-13 victory despite gaining just 121 total yards.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klein's 2 TDs help Kansas St. slip past Texas

events.name: Kentucky Wildcats at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Aaron Murray threw a touchdown pass to Marlon Brown on the first play of the fourth quarter, Blair Walsh kicked four field goals and No. 13 Georgia beat Kentucky 19-10 on Saturday to clinch a spot in the SEC championship game.

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Kirk Cousins threw for 273 yards and three touchdowns in just over a half as  Michigan State moved a step closer to the Big Ten championship game with a 55-3 rout of Indiana on Saturday.

events.name: Nebraska Cornhuskers at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Denard Robinson threw two touchdown passes and ran for two scores to help Michigan rout Nebraska 45-17 Saturday.

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: Montee Ball rushed for 224 yards and Wisconsin forced four turnovers in a 28-17 comeback win against Illinois on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wisconsin's Ball scores 30th TD, tops Illinois

events.name: Colorado State Rams at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Antoine Hicks, Ed Wesley and Matthew Tucker ran for touchdowns and Tank Carder returned an interception 69 yards for a touchdown, helping TCU win at least a share of the Mountain West title with a 34-10 victory over Colorado State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: TCU wins to clinch share of Mountain West title

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Penn State won for the first time since coach Joe Paterno was fired, with Stephfon Green running for two touchdowns and the Nittany Lions' solid defense holding Ohio State scoreless in the second half of a 20-14 victory Saturday.

events.name: Samford Bulldogs at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Auburn survived a scare from Samford, but reeled off 14 straight points in the fourth quarter to close out a 35-16 win on Saturday.

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Kevin Parks ran 10 yards for a touchdown with 1:16 left Saturday to give Virginia the lead and Florida State's Dustin Hopkins missed a 42-yard field-goal attempt in the closing seconds as the Cavaliers upset Florida State 14-13.
headlines.shortLinkText: Virginia upsets Florida State with late touchdown

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Connecticut Huskies

headlines.description: Teddy Bridgewater threw for 174 yards and scored two rushing touchdowns as Louisville beat Connecticut 34-20 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Louisville handles UConn to maintain title hopes

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Dan Persa threw for 216 yards and two touchdowns, and Northwestern won its fourth straight, beating Minnesota 28-13 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Persa launches Northwestern to bowl eligibility

events.name: Cincinnati Bearcats at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Freshman Jawan Jamison rushed for a career-high 200 yards and two touchdowns and surprising Rutgers moved into a share of first place in the Big East Conference with a 20-3 victory over Cincinnati on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rutgers shares Big East lead after rout of Cincy

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Ryan Tannehill threw for three touchdowns, Cyrus Gray ran for three more and Texas A&M got an easy 61-7 win over mistake-prone Kansas on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas A&M routs Kansas, becomes bowl eligible

events.name: Akron Zips at Buffalo Bulls

headlines.description: Buffalo 51, Akron 10

events.name: Iowa Hawkeyes at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description: James Vandenberg threw three touchdown passes, including two to Marvin McNutt, to help Iowa defeat Purdue 31-21 on Saturday for the Hawkeyes' first road win of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa beats Purdue for first road win of season

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: David Sims rushed for two touchdowns, quarterback Tevin Washington added 136 yards rushing and a long, late scoring run, and Georgia Tech held on to beat Duke 38-31 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington's late TD helps Ga. Tech survive

events.name: Furman Paladins at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Florida allowed a season-high 22 points in the first quarter before storming back behind a career-best four touchdown passes from John Brantley to secure a 54-32 win over Furman on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida shakes off scary start to roll by Furman

events.name: James Madison Dukes at UMass Minutemen

headlines.description: James Madison 34, UMass 17

events.name: Army Black Knights at Temple Owls

headlines.description: Temple 42, Army 14

events.name: Eastern Michigan Eagles at Kent State Golden Flashes

headlines.description: Spencer Keith threw a 70-yard touchdown pass to Tyshon Goode, and then Sidney Saulter's interception at the goal-line with 1:47 left preserved Kent State's 28-22 win over Eastern Michigan on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kent St. holds off E. Michigan for 4th straight win

Minot State Beavers at UT San Antonio Roadrunners

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Tanner Price threw for 320 yards and three touchdowns, and Wake Forest snapped a three-game losing streak to become bowl eligible with a 31-10 victory over Maryland on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wake Forest halts slide to become bowl eligible

headlines.description: Appalachian St. 28, Elon 24

events.name: Miami Hurricanes at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: Jake Wieclaw's second field goal of the game, a 36-yarder as time expired, gave Miami a 6-3 victory over South Florida and made the Hurricanes bowl eligible on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Canes bowl eligible as USF loses Daniels, game

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: James Franklin accounted for four touchdowns and got the go-ahead score on a 9-yard run with 2:22 remaining as Missouri, minus suspended coach Gary Pinkel, rallied past Texas Tech 31-27 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Without Pinkel, Missouri rallies past Texas Tech

events.name: Washington Huskies at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: Sean Mannion threw for 339 yards and two touchdowns as Oregon State beat Washington 38-21 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mannion throws for 339 yards, leads Oregon St.

headlines.description: Rice 19, Tulane 7

headlines.description: Troy 34, FAU 7

events.name: Navy Midshipmen at San Jose State Spartans

headlines.description: San Jose St. 27, Navy 24

events.name: Boston College Eagles at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Jonas Gray rushed for a touchdown, David Ruffer kicked three field goals and Notre Dame recovered an onside kick with just under 2 minutes to play to hold off Boston College 16-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Notre Dame holds on to get past Boston College

headlines.description: Sam Houston St. 36, Texas St. 14

events.name: Utah Utes at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Coleman Petersen kicked a 38-yard field goal in the first overtime as Utah beat Washington State 30-27 on a snowy Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah overcomes weather, tops Wash. St. in OT

events.name: Vanderbilt Commodores at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Eric Gordon intercepted a pass by Jordan Rodgers and returned it 90 yards for a touchdown in overtime as Tennessee escaped Vanderbilt with a 27-21 win on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gordon interception seals overtime win for Vols

events.name: Colorado Buffaloes at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Kevin Prince threw for 225 yards and hit tight end Joseph Fauria with two of his career-high four touchdown passes, and UCLA moved within one victory of an improbable Pac-12 South title with a 45-6 win over Colorado on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UCLA rolls, within one win of Pac-12 South title
